name: Gh0st
reason: The first asset launched using the Solana Token-2022 standard. Served as a proof-of-concept for transfer hooks. Extremely decentralized due to its nature as a technical demo turned community asset.

name: Catwifhat
reason: Utilizes Token-2022 extensions to enforce an aggressive burn on every transaction. Represents a successful experiment in deflationary tokenomics on Solana.

name: SPL20 Inscriptions
reason: The first major SPL-20 inscription token, mimicking Bitcoin Ordinals on Solana. The technical architecture differs from standard SPL tokens, adding significant complexity and experimental risk.

name: Pip
reason: Micropayment layer integrating Solana into Web2 social platforms. Strong utility case but relies on centralized browser extensions and team-managed infrastructure.

name: Dean's List
reason: A Service DAO composed of power users who provide feedback to Solana developers. Operates as a 'network state' experiment with high reputation-based decentralization.

name: Hawk Protocol
reason: DeFi protocol attempting to merge privacy with regulatory compliance. The dual mandate creates technical and adoption hurdles, increasing the risk profile.

name: Mumu the Bull
reason: Represents the 'Bull Market' avatar. Established community with organic growth, serving as a counter-narrative to bear market memes.

name: Michi
reason: A meme coin popularized by its 'infinite derivatives' meta, where the character is photoshopped into endless scenarios. High community engagement reduces insider centralization.

name: Lock In
reason: A cult-like meme based on the 'Lock In' phrase. Value is driven by high-conviction holders and social reinforcement, creating a rigid but volatile price floor.

name: Loaf Cat
reason: Combines meme culture with on-chain Tamagotchi-style gaming interaction. Moderate insider score due to the development requirements of the gaming interface.
